executeOnceSafely

public static void executeOnceSafely(Operation operation)
                              throws DataException,
                                     LogicException
Worker lifecycle management hack, because certain legacy operation implementations do not allow multiple worker executions between init/open and close.
This assumes that the provided instance has already called Worker.init(gr.interamerican.bo2.arch.Provider) and Worker.open().
This method makes sure that the operation gets closed regardless of whether execute() completes successfully.

Parameters:
operation -
Throws:
DataException
LogicException
